-- Monti Says There Are No Obstacles to Tax Dialogue With Swiss
-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 2012-05-11T15:05:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-11/monti-says-there-are-no-obstacles-to-tax-dialogue-with-swiss.html
Prime Minister  Mario Monti  said there
are no longer any obstacles to starting talks on tax and
financial issues with Switzerland.  Monti, speaking at a press conference in Rome today, said
he will soon meet with Swiss President Eveline Widmer-Schlumpf
to discuss the matter.  He said previous obtacles to such talks included a review
by the European Union on tax agreements between member states
and Switzerland and Swiss rules on Italian citizens working in
the Alpine country.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lorenzo Totaro in Rome at 
 ltotaro@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
